  <recipe>
    <name>Kims Lentil Dhal</name>
    <source>www.taste.com.au/recipes/14107/lentil+dhal</source>
    <preparation>Step1: Place Lentils, ginger, bay leaves and cinnamon in a large
saucepan with 3 cups of cold water. Bring to boil, reduce the heat
to medium and simmer, stirring to prevent sticking for 10-12 
minutes. Discard spices and set aside.

Step2: Heat the butter in a large frying pan over a medium high
heat. Add the onion and cook for 3 minutes. Stir in the garlic, 
turmeric, cumin, garam masala and chili flakes and cook for
a further minute or until fragrant. Stir in the lemon juice and
season to taste with salt.

Step3: Add the lentils to the pan and mix well. Cook for a further
3 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from the heat. Stir in 
coriander and serve hot with naan bread or pappadums.</preparation>
    <potions>4</potions>
    <portions>4</portions>
    <cook>Kim Meredith</cook>
