    <name>Kartoffel-Kohlrabisalat</name>
    <source>selfmade</source>
    <preparation>1. Put the potatoes to cook (preferrably steaming)

2. Shred kohlrabi into flakes and season with soy sauce,
fish sauce, sesame oil and freshly ground mustard seeds.

3. When potatoes are finished, peel them and cut into slices.
Mix potato slices with kohlrabi salad. Adapt seasoning with
salt, butter and (Styrian) pumpkin oil.</preparation>
